><span class=title> A Sermon</span><hr size=1> Hello. I am here today to speak of an ideal, one that permeates all aspects of life and one that forms the actual basis of a wizard's power. Hate.<br>
<br>
Hate is often spoken of in less than glowing terms. It's disparaged, wrongly because of it's negative connotations. Poeple say &quot;it's wrong to hate!&quot; and certainly on the surface, that seems to make sense. Hate must be bad, right? Surely nothing good can come of Hate, right? Please... <br>
<br>
The definition of &quot;good&quot; has become skewed over the centuries by treehugging ninnies, druids mostly, who have aimed that word squarely at everything they hold dear. Tunare is &quot;good&quot;. Nature is &quot;good&quot;. Rubbish. &quot;Good&quot; is simply a subjective term, as is &quot;bad&quot;. It's all dependant on where you're coming from. Notions of &quot;good&quot; and &quot;bad&quot; are just ways of framing the debate to the advantage of the popular.<br>
<br>
Here's reality. Wizards pursue power and knowledge. To that end, things which accomplish our goals are &quot;good&quot;. Things that obstruct us are &quot;bad&quot;. To Hate that which obstructs our goals is a noble thing, for it provides us motivation to surmount these obstacles. Hate gives us the advantage of fury, which in turn enhances our power. Unfortunately, many foolish people attribute this enhancement to Solusek Ro.<br>
<br>
The fact is, Solusek Ro is himself influenced greatly by Hate. When was the last time you visited the Desert of Ro? Does it look like a reasoned solution to the conflict with Tunare? No. It was savage, utterly motivated by Hate, and beautiful. Yes, beautiful. I've watched many sunsets in the Desert of Ro and they are still among the loveliest sights I've ever seen. Definite change for the better. I salute Lord Ro for his decorating skills. /salute<br>
<br>
However, when it comes to issues of power, Innoruuk is clearly the superior deity. Even Solusek Ro calls upon Hatred to perform his wonders. Strike of Solusek, for example, is powerful...but it is nothing but an overpowered match without Hateful intent. Those of you slavishly devoted to the Burning Prince(and I believe strongly that title came from certain other activities concerning Tunare, but we won't get into that here...) are no doubt foaming at the mouth right now, wishing to stake me out for your Inquisition. If you take a moment to think about it, you will see the Inquisition serves our mutual Lord's purposes well, even if you are somewhat fuddled as to whom you actually serve.<br>
<br>
All praise Innoruuk, our lord and creator! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=vdou>Vdou</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 296<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/03 2:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> Interesting.<br>
