<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Hate gives us the advantage of fury, which in turn enhances our power. Unfortunately, many foolish people attribute this enhancement to Solusek Ro.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am a child of Hate. Hate is a part of my heredity. Yet, I do not need to follow Innoruuk's precepts of destruction and death to attain the power I desire, nor do I need to attend his Church to understand the power of Hate. I have had many conflicts with the Chruch of Innoruuk on this matter, which incidently is why I make the Temple of Solusek Ro my permanent residence.<br>
<br>
What is the nature of power? Hate can motivate you to kill and destroy, but for what purpose? Pure Hatred is as simplistic a creed as you can follow. Furthermore, it is devoid of any redeeming spiritual qualities. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>To that end, things which accomplish our goals are &quot;good&quot;. Things that obstruct us are &quot;bad&quot;. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
HA! Thats on page 34 of the Solusite's Handbook.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If you take a moment to think about it, you will see the Inquisition serves our mutual Lord's purposes well, even if you are somewhat fuddled as to whom you actually serve.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
