Simplistic? Hardly. Say clear, perhaps. Consistant. As for redeeming spiritual qualities, I daresay that depends which charlatan deity you allow to bend your ear this week. Each seems to have their own definitions of virtue and redemption. Most of them expound on ridiculous notions of self sacrifice and pointless servitude. For example, the only reward a servant of Mithaniel Marr can expect is death. They may paint it as &quot;valorous&quot; but the end result is the same...you are dead.<br>
<br>
<br>
