You see! FOOLS, the lot of you! You ADMIRE opposition, you LIKE being thwarted? You are nothing but masochists! Opposition is something to be UTTERLY CRUSHED, not to be admired or treated as noble!<br>
<br>
And in some instances fury is a good thing, but in others it is horribly counterproductive. For example, when in the grips of rage, individuals will say things and do things that at a later date they will regret:  for example, spitting on the feet of one's superior after given an unpleasant command may result in death or excommunication, which is far from conducive to power!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The fact is, Solusek Ro is himself influenced greatly by Hate.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
He experiences hate, and he has strong hatreds, but NEVER, EVER is he motivated by hate. He is motivated by the search for Power, not by lesser emotions. If the search for power involves killing someone He hates, all the better, but never will it be a factor when He makes His Holy Decisions - for to allow emotions to cloud logic is worthy of Erolissi or Innoruuk worshipers, who have the mental capabilities of twelve year old halfling children, and not for mighty wizards or Gods.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
When was the last time you visited the Desert of Ro? Does it look like a reasoned solution to the conflict with Tunare? No. It was savage, utterly motivated by Hate, and beautiful.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nay, it was not MOTIVATED by hate! Indeed, the Great Lord hates Tunare and all of her vile followers, but He moved against them because He realized they would be a threat to the balance of the world - and ultimately, to His Own Magnificent Designs. He relished the action of destroying their homeland, He relished the death and destruction of an ecosystem, but He did NOT let emotion to be the deciding factor in His Holy Actions!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
