<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not so, the Great Lord calls upon Power alone to perform His Holy Wonders, not emotion and other hippy forces! Are you saying that a casual Strike of Solusek at a passing wolf would be in any way less powerful than one by an individual who strongly hates wolves? No, it wouldn't, if anything, the individual motivated solely by hate would be so furious that he would likely botch the spell! Hatred is all well and good, but you must never let it control you - for hatred clouds judgment just as well as love.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
