Not it doesn't, it serves the purposes of the Lord alone. Killing Innoruuk's followers serves only to decrease his influence - the hatred that we show towards you is fueled by our desire for power, it is not fuel in and of itself. We shall butcher every last one of you, the Bertoxxulous worshipers, Brell Serilis worshipers, followers of Bristlebane, Cazic-Thule, Erolissi Marr, Karana, Mithaniel Marr, Prexus, Quellious, Rallos Zek, Rodcet Nife, Tunare, Veeshan, and Innoruuk, you shall be made to REPENT for your sins before you die, and you shall be sent to the endless, flaming halls of the Great Lord's Holy Dungeons! And after you are all finished with, the Great Lord shall turn his attention on your impotent godling, and destroy his plane, slay his servants, and finally, crush Innoruuk beneath His Holy Will! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aurianne>Aurianne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 3420<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/03 6:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> Inny's an even bigger pussy than Solusek Weenie-Boy. That is all. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khaymus>Khaymus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/28/03 8:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> Eamin...you mistake pointless Hate, stupid Hate, with truly focused Hate. You speak of trivialities like betrayal and deception as if that was TRULY Hate.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>for example, spitting on the feet of one's superior after given an unpleasant command may result in death or excommunication, which is far from conducive to power!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
