A rank, arrogant amateur might spit at the feet of one's superior. A Master of Hate, however, would have the commander quietly eliminated and arrange to take his rank.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You worshipers of Innoruuk simply can't grasp that good and evil are really irrelevant. The only thing that matters is Power, confining yourself to a short-sighted, druido-clerical moral code is utter foolishness.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I thought I made a good case that good and evil are meaningless concepts within the scope of a wizard's mission. I agree, it isn't about good and bad, not about right and wrong...it's about power(and a cookie to anyone who can identify that quote).<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Innoruuk is an impotent weakling. When has Innoruuk done a great or godlike feat in his existence?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Innoruuk created the Tier'Dal. Remind me...what exactly has Solusek Ro created, other than an enormously tacky Temple?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You ADMIRE opposition, you LIKE being thwarted? You are nothing but masochists! Opposition is something to be UTTERLY CRUSHED, not to be admired or treated as noble!<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Hardly. I said Hatred of obstruction, Hatred of one's enemies is noble, because it provides us motivation to surmount those obstacles. Without enemies and obstacles, you will grow into power without exercising it to the fullest. You will be crippled, mentally and magically. And then someone like me will come along and crush you utterly.<br>
<br>
