<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
The only true way to greater power is through destruction or the death of one's enemies. Even Solusek Ro gets it. Why don't you?<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So, you think that you can win debates by shamelessly stealing pages out of the Book of Flames and pretending like Innoruuk is the one who wrote them? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khaymus>Khaymus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 203<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/03 2:54 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>What's your point again? You claim that an act of hate, carried out PERFECTLY, will gain you power - and I claim that an act of gaining power will gain power. You're just saying &quot;Look, when I killed a gnoll pup the Qeynos Guards liked me more! Obviously, the only way to make them like me is to kill gnoll pups!&quot; Acts of hate gain you power on occasion, purely by chance, but purely by chance isn't a good way to do business.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Not perfectly...merely carefully. Hatred is not the total recklessness you seem to think it is. True Hate simmers beneath the surface. You speak of generic notions of &quot;gaining power&quot;, but not of your underlying motivations. Power for power's own sake is mere potential, fallow and barren in and of itself. Power for Hate's sake has focus, action, and results. Let me ask you something...are you familiar with Alexander? Power is not an end to itself...it is a means. Without focus, a solid, measurable goal, power withers. It dies. I destroy life with Hate in my heart, and when I've extinguished every unfaithful life on Norrath, I will carry my mission to other worlds, if it pleases Innoruuk.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Oh really?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes. Really. That tome admits that he is siphoning power. I believe he created these fiends about as far as I believe Tunare created the goblins. And I still think that machine was designed and built by gnomes, who are clearly the finest craftsmen(I have commissioned a few to work on a death ray). Probably agnostics, as they tend to think more clearly than you Solusites.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>If Innoruuk isn't evil, Bertoxxulous and Cazic-Thule aren't evil either. Being evil isn't necessarily a bad thing, it's just not being neutral.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You would have a hard time painting Solusek Ro into the &quot;neutral&quot; camp with the atrocities he's committed prior and the ones he plans to commit. Of course, I rather like your Master's plan, as it saves me a lot of time killing the feebleminded. I already have my new spell,  Shadowbane Gate, scribed and ready.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>He rewarded cleverness and ambition: but then He punished stupidity. You don't plot against your lord when you have a mere fraction of His power. I suppose Innoruuk respects stupidity, though.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Of course you don't, and I didn't mean to imply these men weren't stupid. Their choice in deity should bear mute witness to that fact. Innoruuk does respect a good, diabolical plot. He Hates it, of course, but he does not punish it. Look at the example of Lanys T'Val. Even in death, in failure, she was brought forth and used to Innoruuk's ends. Waste not, want not.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Nay, He was furious at their treachery. He stripped them of the powers that He had bestowed upon them.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The powers &quot;He&quot; bestowed. That would make you a priest or a false wizard. Wizardly powers come from within the self, and are not issued by gods. If Solusek is creating pseudowizards, that's another problem entirely. Tell me...did Solusek Ro bestow your powers upon you, too? Do you possess no power of your own? I use my powers in Innoruuk's service, but they are the doing of no god. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Innoruuk, God of Hatred, is among the most minor of all the godly pantheon, so minor, in fact, that he isn't even parly to Solusek Ro's and Rallos Zek's plans to destroy Norrath.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
That is a matter of opinion. Others would say Innoruuk poses a far greater, more insidious threat than your penny ante, can't-get-along-without-Daddy's-power god you worship.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>When the time is ripe: attacking before you are prepared is idiotic and worthy only of a follower of Innoruuk<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Sticks and stones. It seems you plan much the same as my example above with the superior. Tell me...do you plan to seize his power as well after his threat is dealt with? You would do well to watch your back. Others have been harshly punished for such &quot;blasphemous&quot; thoughts. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>A perfect swordsman can use his sword to great effect, but does that mean it is the best way to attain his goal? In some situations, would not a bow or a staff serve his purposes better? The Great Lord has the sword, and the bow, and the staff: Innoruuk has merely the sword.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Innoruuk is not alone. He has access to all these avenues and more through his loyal followers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Gnoll pups hate me. Why aren't I dead yet? Hate without power is useless and impotent.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If those gnoll pups are allowed to grow into something more fearsome, their Hatred may indeed be your undoing. The thing you are missing is Hate's role as motivation. Hatred of you can eventually forge a gnoll pup into a powerful leader of his kind, bent on one goal...your death. He can motivate his people, by Hatred, to murder Erudites in massive numbers. The end result of a gnoll pup's Hatred of you could be the absolute destruction of your homeland. This of course won't come to pass because gnolls are notoriously stupid.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>This makes no sense. You claim that hatred is the road to power (despite it being a nonsensical druidic claim), while I claim that power is the road to power. Hating people has nowhere been proven to gain power, but searching for power most certainly has.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I Hate people. Because I Hate people, I seek out the means to end their lives. I seek ever greater means to end even more lives. The means to that end is often magic. Hate is the motive, not the means. Innoruuk's blessings do, however, augment wizardly power. Anger and Fury do indeed strengthen magic. Several magical items carry this power, but are wrongfully attributed to Solusek Ro.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So, you think that you can win debates by shamelessly stealing pages out of the Book of Flames and pretending like Innoruuk is the one who wrote them? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I'm not pretending. If you can't see Innoruuk's influence among the pages of your own sacred text...well, far be it for me to interfere with your &quot;learning&quot;. Absorb from the book what you can. I have no doubt which lessons will stick fast. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ikeya>Ikeya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<br>Stamping Out Stupidity</span><br>  Posts: 3258<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/03 4:20 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> Hate is a treasonous emotion.  For it is the man who guides the Hate, but the Hate that guides the man.  Even the greatest masters will succumb to its unrelenting power.  You claim that Hate can be mastered and used for one's own gain.  Yet, like all emotions, it too will betray you.  You attempt to subjugate the unconquerable.  It will lead to your demise.<br>
<br>
The followers of Solusek Ro, however, know their place.  We seek power.  We gather power.  But we do not attempt to manipulate it.  We do not try to lord over it.  For the power we find is power given to us from the Burning Prince.  We submit ourselves to the power and to his will.  And through that, we are rewarded.  Instead of attempting to control the uncontrolable, we gather it around us and let it use us.  We are but mere vessels for the power and glory of Solusek Ro.  It is not up to us to decide how to use it.<br>
<br>
You attempt to control the power that your emotions give you.  And it is there that you are folly.<br>
<br>
-Ikeya <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khaymus>Khaymus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/03 6:01 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>You attempt to control the power that your emotions give you. And it is there that you are folly.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Control, no. Harness, channel...yes.<br>
<br>
As for the rest...if you truly derive your powers from Solusek Ro...take off your robes and put on leather armor, for you are no better truly than a druid. Break your ties with Solusek Ro and seek out power that is yours and yours alone...and not bound to the will of another. Until it is so, you are little better than a slave on a leash. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eaminwhitefalcon@graffeswizardcompilation>Eamin Whitefalcon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist<BR>¡Viva la inquisición!</span><br>  Posts: 6369<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/03 10:35 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Power is not an end to itself...it is a means.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And so, we see your heart! This is where we differ. A follower of the Great Lord believes that Power is the means and the end, the alpha and the omega, it encompasses the entire goal and not simply the last stage. By gaining power, one can gain more power, and more, and more, in a never-ending process. All other goals, be they the destruction of enemies, the saving of loved ones, or the gaining of knowledge, are mere distractions on the road to absolute Power, they are fools' gold in the mine, sent to cause the true Wizard's mind to wander from what should be his only goal.<br>
<br>
You worship a god of distraction and tricks, the nymph in the woods, who lures the warrior away from the maiden he is to save. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=whizbangdustyboots>Whizbang Dustyboots</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder Arcanist<BR>Gnomus Originalus</span><br>  Posts: 12244<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/30/03 1:49 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Sermon</span><hr size=1> Power is a tool to an end.<br>
<br>
Hate is an end that destroys itself, thus invalidating itself.<br>
<br>
You're all fools, blinded by your own rhetoric. <p><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=49189" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.lby3.com/eq/whiz/whiz_toon.gif" height="104" width="390" alt="stats" border=0></a>
